Clean Data:

- Inspect the dataset before cleaning it.
  Check:
  column names,
  data types,
  missing-value counts,
  duplicate rows,
  a few sample records.

- Check the actual column names first.
  - Column names are case-sensitive.

- Handle missing data before converting to lowercase.

- Fill missing values first, then apply lowercase formatting.

- Do not convert directly with astype(int) unless the column is guaranteed clean.
  It will fail if the column contains: - missing values, - decimal values, - text, - invalid entries.

- First convert invalid values to missing values, decide whether to remove or replace them, and then convert the cleaned values to integers.
